# The `else` Block

What if we want to run *different* code when the condition is false? We provide a Plan B using the `else` keyword.

```swift
let isRaining = false

if isRaining {
    print("Bring an umbrella! вҳ”пёҸ")
} else {
    print("Wear your sunglasses! рҹ•¶пёҸ")
}
```
Because `isRaining` is `false`, Swift skips the first block and runs the `else` block instead!

